summary:
**Summary of ASX Announcement (HUB24 - Quarterly Report):**  

- **Record FY25 Platform Net Inflows**: $19.8bn (up 25% pcp), including $5.3bn in Q4 (up 7% pcp).  
- **Total FUA**: $136.4bn (up 30% pcp) — Platform FUA $112.7bn (up 34%), PARS FUA $23.7bn (up 16%).  
- **Market Share**: Platform ranked #1 for net inflows (6th consecutive quarter); market share rose to 8.7% (from 7.2% in Mar-24).  
- **Adviser Growth**: 5,097 active advisers (up 13% pcp); 31 new distribution agreements signed in Q4.  
- **Product Launches**: HUB24 Private Invest (HNW solution) launched; Class Super released AI-powered Virtual Mailroom.  
- **Class Super**: Largest annual account growth since FY20 (+8,006 accounts to 215,675).  
- **Customer Satisfaction**: Ranked #1 for adviser NPS and overall satisfaction in Investment Trends report.  

*No capital raising, trading halt, or material structural changes identified.*
